{
  "id": "02493a402dd075d1",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/skelar/a68e435d-e1a4-46d7-a447-8d672e7f8597/application",
    "company": "skelar",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "02493a402dd075d1",
    "department": "Finance",
    "description": "[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/3a2721ac-0cf6-4bb5-a785-483b8d1018c3/Ashby_header.png]\n\nSKELAR is a venture builder that creates international tech businesses according to the guidelines of venture capital investment.\n\n\nWe are looking for a detail-oriented Tax Analyst to join our International Reporting and Tax Compliance team at SKELAR. In this role, you will work with indirect tax matters across multiple jurisdictions and help ensure accurate and scalable tax reporting as the company continues to expand internationally.\n\n\nYou will collaborate with internal teams and external advisors across different countries, working with financial data and tax reporting processes related to VAT / GST / sales tax. The role offers exposure to international tax systems and the opportunity to contribute to building efficient and automated tax processes in a fast-growing global tech environment.\n\n\nIf you enjoy working with data, building structured processes, and improving the way financial reporting works — this role is for you.\n\n\nThe main functions of this role include:\n\n - Support indirect tax reporting processes across multiple jurisdictions, working with the internal team and external advisors who prepare and submit VAT / GST / sales tax filings.\n\n - Collect, organize, and validate financial data and supporting documentation required for tax reporting.\n\n - Prepare and review indirect tax calculations and reports, ensuring completeness and accuracy of data used in tax filings.\n\n - Work with large datasets related to transactions and cross-border operations, helping ensure correct tax treatment.\n\n - Support the team in monitoring regulatory updates and assessing their potential impact on reporting processes.\n\n - Contribute to improving and automating tax reporting workflows, identifying opportunities to increase efficiency and data quality.\n\n - Assist with tax-related aspects of international expansion, helping organize reporting processes as the company enters new markets.\n   \n\nSkills and experience needed to join the board:\n\n - 1–3 years of experience in tax, accounting, finance, or related roles in Big 4 / consulting firms or international companies.\n\n - Basic understanding of indirect taxation principles (VAT / GST / sales tax).\n\n - Strong attention to detail and ability to work with financial data.\n\n - Analytical mindset and ability to structure information clearly.\n\n - Good Excel / Google Sheets skills and comfort working with datasets.\n\n - Structured thinking and strong organizational skills.\n\n - Upper-intermediate English (both written and spoken).\n\n - Proactive attitude and willingness to develop expertise in international tax.\n   \n\nSKELAR is a place for self-realization of talents who are able to create successful companies. We call such companies the next big everything. We believe in their power and scale.\n\nIn addition to our businesses, we have the SKELAR Foundation — a charitable foundation created by company employees. As part of the initiative, we create and finance projects that contribute to overcoming the consequences of the war and the reconstruction of Ukraine.\n\nWe will keep developing tech businesses, conquer global markets, and work for the victory of Ukraine 🇺🇦\n\n\nWhat we offer:\n\n - Competitive salary;\n\n - Significant impact on a rapidly growing business and contribution to how it shapes up;\n\n - Ample career opportunities for ambitious growth and development;\n\n - Working alongside professionals from top local and international companies (Big Law, Big 4, McKinsey, Horizon, Bolt, Didi, etc.);\n\n - Flat organizational structure without hierarchical barriers;\n\n - A possibility to attend internal and external courses, seminars, and access to a corporate library;\n\n - Comfortable working environment with all necessary equipment and complimentary breakfasts, lunches, and snacks in the office;\n\n - 20 days of paid vacation, medical insurance, and a variety of sports activities available for employees.\n\nLet's build the next big everything together.\n\n[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/bf8afb62-59f5-436b-b500-74f06bd0bb6e/Ashby_footer_eng.png]",
